postcontent: Originally issued to the Czech army in 1958, the VZ58 is still in use by both the Czech and Slovak armies, their police and customs agents. title: For Sale/Trade:  Saiga 12 fighting shotgun with full  rail system
postcontent:
*+*+*** Trade for AKs,  RPK,  RPD,  PSL's ***+*+*

These are the same shotguns that were recently banned from import by President Obama. And like all EO bans in the past (Chinese weapons and ammunition by Clinton and then Bush Jr) this ban will likely be in place forever ensuring prices on guns like these will go up. Prices on these will only continue to increase because there is now a finite number in the United States and over time that number will decrease making these more and more valuable with the passing day. The same thing happened in 1986 with machine guns and we have seen how much they have increased in value since then. The recent ban mentions these guns specifically so they will no longer be imported but because they are not banned from sale between individuals their value will continue to rise. 

As far as what I want in trade I have no clue but here are some things I might be interested in:
 Unique firearms
 AKs with cash
 RPK with cash
 RPD
 PSL's
 S&W Shield w/o safety with cash
7.62x25 Tokarev firearms with cash
7.62x54 firearms (No MOSINS or other bolt actions) 

Now on to the interesting stuff.

This Saiga was built with only one intention, to have the most reliable fighting shotgun humanly possible and this one does not disappoint. 

It is a 12 gauge with the reliability that AK's are known for. 

All modifications or parts added were done by a professional to ensure reliability as well as to give you the advantage to win the fight. The HK sights are probably the best sights on the planet for a fighting shotgun. If you have used them you understand this statement. That is why all the big name Saiga builders, like Tromix, install them. It also has a complete rail system installed to allow the use of optics, lasers, VFG's or lights. 

A TAC-47 automatically adjusting gas system was installed. You can run target loads or full power defense loads without any damage and without the excessive, punishing recoil felt by most other defensive shotguns. The TAC-47 ensures the gun is properly gassed ensuring bolt speed is not excessive and thus preventing damage or premature wear. Being properly gassed also reduces the felt recoil, keeps the gun cleaner, keeps you on target and reduces wear. It has ALWAYS been run with a buffer to prevent rear trunion damage and it does not affect reliability at all. I will also include a 6 way manually adjustable gas plug. 

This Saiga 12 was imported by Russian American Armory, the original importer of these shotguns. It has a 19" chrome lined barrel that is threaded for a flash hider and includes and American made one. 

The following modifications have been done: 
•Complete rail system $150
•The FCG, bolt and bolt carrier have had the "glass bolt" mod done. They have been polished to mirror like smoothness. This was done to ensure 100% reliability, not for looks, and this one modification increases the guns reliability substantially. This also makes it easier to lock in a loaded magazine with the bolt forward. $100
•HK sights welded in place with full depth welds. The rear is a REAL HK sight and the front is designed for Saiga shotguns. This cost over $200 for all the parts and labor 
•Installed a TAC-47 automatic gas regulator. This allows you to shoot low brass and full power defense loads in the same magazine without fear of ruining your rear trunion. $50
•US made FCG. The trigger started out as a dual hook trigger and the second hook was turned into a over travel stop. This is the BEST AK trigger you will ever pull and it does it with the factory hammer spring to maintain 100% reliable ignition. The FCG costs $40 but with the additional work it would cost over $75 to duplicate.
•Billet aluminum trigger guard. $35
•Includes an American made flash hider. $35
•Picatinny rail installed in the rear sight slot for optics use. $50
•ACE 9.5" stock. $65
•ACE rear trunion block. $45
•MOLOT grip (the best grip on the planet for an AK). $10
•Vertical forward grip $20

I will include all magazines I have for this shotgun and all magazines have been tested for 100% reliability.
•Three ProMags, 2 of which have been fitted to the gun and are 100% reliable. One is new in the package. $90
•Two SGM magazines, both fitted. One is a 10 round and one is an 8 rounds. They are 100% reliable. $90
•Three 5 round magazines, one factory, one KeepShooting and one ProMag cut down to hold 5 rounds. $30

All parts, magazines and labor would cost over $1,200 to duplicate and that does not include the value of the shotgun itself. Comparable shotguns are selling for $1,500-$1,800 on Gunbroker.

Here is one I would consider comparable on GB that SOLD for $1,500.
http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=437730358
But this one doesn't have HK sights, the auto gas block, a bunch of magazines, the polished bolt and carrier or the trigger work mine does. 

And here is another one that SOLD for $1,700 but, again, without any of the modifications , magazines or add ons mine has.
http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=438314737
We have already seen a rise in selling prices since then and once the retailers run out these will double almost over night.

You will not find a better, or more reliable, fighting shotgun. No expense was spared because this gun was going to protect my family.

I will answer ANY questions you have as well as take any additional pictures you might want. I can meet at any public range in Knoxville to allow any potential buyer to shoot the shotgun, you will not be disappointed. Please no tire kickers as trips to the range are an ordeal for me. And you must provide the ammo. It will shoot 2 3/4" as well as 3" shells.

If you ever wanted a Saiga fighting shotgun now is the time to get them because they are only going to go up in price. Right now will be the lowest they will ever be. And this will also be an investment you can use because most desirable guns outperform the stock market. Or buy it, list it on Gunbroker and make $300-$500 within a week. Go look at what Saiga 12 shotguns are selling for right now.

title: For Sale:  Sig Tac Stabilizing Brace SB15
postcontent:
SIG SAUER® introduces the SB15 Pistol Stabilizing Brace, a shooter's aid that is designed to improve the single-handed shooting performance of buffer tube equipped pistols. Made from high-quality, elasto-polymer, the SB15 is manufactured to close tolerances and fits all pistols equipped with a pistol buffer tube 1.0" - 1.2" in diameter. The Pistol Stabilizing Brace uses the operator's forearm to provide stable support, thereby minimizing accuracy-robbing spin and shift. A flexible cuff with two adjustable nylon straps allows the SB15 to be custom fit to any user. This veteran-designed and U.S.-manufactured accessory enhances accuracy and reduces felt recoil when using a pistol. ATF has reviewed this product and determined that attaching the SB15 to a firearm does not alter the classification of the firearm or subject the firearm to NFA control. A portion of the proceeds from the sale of every Pistol Stabilizing Brace goes to support the veterans of HAVA (Honored American Veterans Afield). www.honoredveterans.org Note: The ATF has specifically determined that this accessory is a brace to be used on pistols.
